  "text": "Turn the volume all the way up! Round of 16, 6 July 2026 — and England survived a spirited Mexican fightback to win a five-goal thriller. A place in the quarter-finals was the prize, and England had to earn it the hard way against a Mexico side that simply would not lie down.\n\n36' — Jude Bellingham buried it, 0–1! 38' — Jude Bellingham lashed it home, 0–2! 43' — Julián Quiñones made no mistake, 1–2! 60' — Harry Kane from the spot found the net, 1–3! 69' — Raúl Jiménez from the spot smashed it in, 2–3!\n\nJude Bellingham's rapid first-half double — two goals in as many minutes — put England in what looked like comfortable control. Julián Quiñones pulled one back before the break to reopen the tie, and the nerves began to jangle. Harry Kane's penalty restored the two-goal cushion, but Raúl Jiménez's own spot-kick set up a frantic finish that England just about held onto. It was end-to-end, occasionally chaotic, and exactly the kind of test a would-be contender needs to pass.\n\nYou could feel the tension crackle around the ground with every attack.\n\nThis is knockout football at its rawest — win, or fly home.\n\nFULL-TIME: Mexico 2–3 England! England march on, Mexico head home heartbroken — and here's the beautiful part: every goal, every minute you just heard is locked on-chain and verified by TxLINE. No hot air, no guesswork, just receipts. What. A. Game!",
